stories.title: New boy Singh sets up India
stories.summary:
If Sachin Tendulkar provided the early excitement in the ICC KnockOut quarter-final match against Australia on Saturday, the second half of the
innings belonged to Yuvraj Singh who hammered out 84 as India reached 266 for
nine off their 50 overs
